body: I dont understand the story AT ALL

The mystery of the girl and the tunnels are a decent hook. I like the slice of life sections where the main character goes out to eat and do his job.

But dear God the execution is awful. No one explains anything because they're too horny. The doctor says she's treating the girl but doesn't explain what for. The main character doesn't pursue more answers either so he's not compelling as a protagonist. He just comes off as stunningly stupid.

And when some of the mysteries do get uncovered, it's boring as all hell. The girl was treated because she was beaten up because she held some secret information. Wow, I could not care less. The art is passable but not great. Overall 2/10. Not worth your time.

SPOILERS AHEAD: 1-Yeah the doc dies. 2-Yeah, Main LI is kinda Immortal. Part of an experiment that couldn't be replicated. 3-The main villain dies because of friendly fire and run over by a train. They have a nice political speech half second volume. Kojima would be proud. 4-The end is bittersweet IMO. No NTR or FB stuff. It happens like 30 years in the future. MC and Main Li end up together and he works for a delivery company in a secluded road near a village. He gets older, she won't, and they say to everyone they are dad and daughter. Ishoku Dougen avoids to show his face until last frame.They never have kids. If you read Boku no Seinen Koukennin you will understand a reference or two. Same weird slice of life vibe. P.s. yeah, no face mask, no glasses for main LI mid book. MC is plain stupid and just for that this loses some points. BTW Ishoku is almost 60 YO and used helpers to do this stuff... So yeah, there is that.

I have a few nitpick, though.
The secret of the Tunnel is out, and I like how it actually seemed plausible and down to earth. 

My issue is just that, the horror aspects of this just got thrown through the window as soon as they explained it. The Tunnel is no longer scary when you KNOW there's nothing really out there.


Also.. Cold skin, hypnotic eyes, and is prohibited from going outside. Even at a first glance you could tell that these are the characteristic of a vampire, are they going to spin this around and just turn her into a girl with a special bloodline?
I don't mind it (since this kinda gives me Code Geass vibes) but I really do hope that some supernatural stuff would happen eventually.

Alright here's what I think would happen: That cult leader is likely not Fugaku (the politician). According to Aya, the girl was captured and abused physically by Fugaku. Sure, the cult leader recognized her, but he clearly recognized her from somewhere else. Judging by the name he gives her
